-{"id":"flywheel_connectors-q0y8h","title":"fcp-kubernetes: const fn str matches break fcp-e2e package test builds","description":"**File**: connectors/kubernetes/src/connector.rs:1424-1465, 2964-2985

**Symptom**: The user-requested verification command `CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/fcp-p3-r1 rch exec -- cargo test -p fcp-conformance -p fcp-e2e` fails before reaching the touched tests because `fcp-e2e` pulls `fcp-kubernetes` as a dev-dependency and `fcp-kubernetes` no longer compiles on the current nightly.

**Compiler errors**:
```
error[E0658]: cannot match on `str` in constant functions
  --> connectors/kubernetes/src/connector.rs:1424:9
error: `PartialEq` is not yet stable as a const trait
  --> connectors/kubernetes/src/connector.rs:1424:9
...
error: could not compile `fcp-kubernetes` (lib) due to 102 previous errors
```

**Root cause**: multiple `const fn` bodies use `matches!` over `&str` literals. On the current toolchain, `str` equality inside `const fn` still requires unstable const-trait support, so these match expressions are rejected.

**Why it matters**: unrelated `fcp-e2e` verification lanes are blocked by a connector compile failure outside their test target.

**Fix plan**: replace the `matches!`-based string switches in those `const fn` helpers with non-const helpers, or rewrite them to avoid `&str` pattern matching in `const fn` entirely. Then add a focused compile/test lane that exercises `fcp-kubernetes` from the `fcp-e2e` package boundary so this regression is caught earlier.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-21T05:03:10.514679Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-04-21T20:35:06.085884Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["build","connectors","kubernetes"],"comments":[{"id":2812,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-q0y8h","author":"jemanuel","text":"Fixed commit f8712801: dropped const from is_secret_mutation, is_system_namespace, is_shell_binary, approval_for_operation in connectors/kubernetes/src/connector.rs. item_type_name kept as const fn (matches on enum variants, not str). Verified: cargo build -p fcp-kubernetes clean; cargo test -p fcp-kubernetes --lib 514/514 pass; cargo build -p fcp-e2e --tests compiles clean. Unblocks P4 + fcp-e2e verification lanes.","created_at":"2026-04-21T14:23:34Z"},{"id":2817,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-q0y8h","author":"jemanuel","text":"Verified: fix landed in f8712801; only item_type_name remains const (matches enum variants, not str). Bead complete.","created_at":"2026-04-21T20:05:57Z"},{"id":2818,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-q0y8h","author":"jemanuel","text":"Not const-fn. fcp-kubernetes builds clean on current nightly. Actual fcp-e2e test-build failure: several *_compliance_e2e.rs files call verifier.verify(&req.capability_token, ...) passing &CapabilityToken after the consuming verify() migration in d090e532 changed the signature to take owned CapabilityToken. Affected: clickup, dropbox, mcp_bridge, sendgrid at :177/:192/:299. Different bead needed: mass-rewrite the e2e compliance tests to clone/consume the token before verify(). Unclaiming.","created_at":"2026-04-21T20:35:06Z"}]}
